title: 2006 Minnesota's 5th congressional district election
added: Special attention were drawn to Fine's comments after Ellison had won the primary, when he stated "I’m extremely concerned about Keith Ellison, Keith Hakim, Keith X Ellison, Keith Ellison Muhammad", referring to various [[pseudonyms]] Ellison had used when he was in college.<ref name=NYT>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/08/us/politics/08muslim.html|title=Democrat Poised to Become First Muslim in Congress|website=The New York Times|last1=MacFarquhar|first1=Neil|date=October 8, 2006|accessdate=March 16, 2021|author-link=Neil MacFarquhar}}</ref> These remarks were seen by some as [[racist]], one of Fine's brothers, Robert Fine, wrote a letter to Ellison denouncing his brother's comments.<ref name=NYT/>
